Additionally, the paper may be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as kernel methods are used in various AI applications such as natural language processing and robotics. 

The paper's focus on centered alignment as a similarity measure between kernels or kernel matrices may also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves algorithmic development.
